OSOGBO – Protest has greeted the Osun State Command of Nigeria Security And Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) over the road show by Minister of Interior where exchange of gunshots were recorded between the minister’s security aides and some armed political thugs allegedly sponsored by another group. The protesters under the aegis of National Association of Osun State Students (NAOSS) armed witg placards with different inscriptions stormed the entrance of the command condemning the road show by the minister. They argued that during the road show, several gunshots were fired which causes panic and fear among the residents. Robbers Kill UBTH Optometrist Doctor In Benin Edo Communities Protest Alleged Incessant Invasion, Killing By… Some of the placards read, “NSCDC stop threatening our people, “NSCDC are safe”, “NSCDC We Are Having You For Peace Not To Kill Our People”, “Stop brutality against our people among others. The protesters were also chanting war songs waiting for the Commandant to address them before departing the scene. Details….